Lightly whisk {1ea|egg}.
Add 1/3rd {250ml|flour}, mixing until just combined, followed by 1/3rd {1ml|milk}, mixing again.
Repeat until all the {flour} and {milk} are combined.
Splash in fizzy {lemonade} until the mixture has the consistency of warm honey.
Let stand 10-30 minutes.

Heat {butter} in a non-stick frypan to grease.
Spoon batter into the hot pan and swirl to spread the misxture out thinly.
Fry until the top firms up, we want a lace-like brown pattern on the bottom.
Flip and fry briefly until the second side is blistered.

Serve with {{to serve|Maple syrup/Lemon and brown sugar/Nutella}}.

